title: What happened the last time Mets' Jacob deGrom and Los Angeles Dodgers' Zack Greinke matched up?
text:
NEW YORK — Jacob deGrom and Zack Greinke are set to clash in Game 5 of the National League Division Series between the Mets and Los Angeles Dodgers on Thursday at Dodger Stadium, but it's not the first time the two right-handers have matched up this season.
Back in July, deGrom and Greinke faced off at Citi Field in what was billed as a marquee pitching matchup. Greinke entered the game with a 43 2/3 inning scoreless streak, but deGrom himself snapped it with an run-scoring groundout in the third inning.
PLUS : Clayton Kershaw on Zack Greinke vs. Jacob deGrom
In the end, deGrom also bested Greinke on the mound , firing 7 1/3 scoreless innings while walking two and striking out eight. DeGrom allowed just two hits — a single to Greinke in the third and another single to Andre Ethier in the fifth.
Greinke, meanwhile, gave up two runs on four hits over seven innings.
Neither pitcher received a decision in the game, but the Mets went on to win, 3-2, thanks to Juan Uribe's walk-off RBI single in the bottom of the 10th inning .
Will deGrom be able to upstage Greinke again on Thursday? Stay tuned.
